{
  "stem": "18102.3",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 54.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a vivid memory in-- of mine, because it was so thrilling, I mean, absolutely thrilling, the things I saw.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I saw Lenin in his tomb, embalmed in his tomb, sitting as if he was lifelike and this soldier standing in erect attention around this-- the mausoleum that he, he lie in.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and we, we came to, to look at him, as tourists.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'll never forget that scene.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know-- God knows where Lenin is today.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But then he was-- you know, it was a place of honor, extreme honor.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we saw that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So all of this was thrilling.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The day we left for Moscow-- we were in Moscow three days.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And my father said he never, never-- the feeling that someone was following him never left his side, even though we were seeing all these sights and touring.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And, and, in fact, that feeling was transmitted to me, that all was not quite as the surface would seem.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I'm sure he was right, that people followed us, and, and we were watched and so forth.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But the day we left was very cold.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And Moscow can get quite cold.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And this was December.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And, in fact, it was into the-- probably the second week of December.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I know that because we celebrated New Year's-- or at least I have a memory of that-- on the train.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So it must have been just before we hit Vladivostok that we welcomed January 1, 1941 on the train in the trans-Siberian railroad.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Anyway, the next episode was my memories of that train ride, which, of course, stand out in my mind and will forever.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because, I mean, how many people spend two weeks on a train, literally two weeks on a train?",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
